  "title": "Executive, Fundraising (Welfare)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conceptualize, plan, and organize events and activities to achieve optimal outcomes.</li>\n  <li>Design and implement fundraising initiatives, including digital campaigns, signature events, and in-person engagements, to meet fundraising goals.</li>\n  <li>Develop and execute strategies to effectively promote events and fundraising efforts.</li>\n  <li>Manage all aspects of event logistics — from vendor selection and coordination to budgeting and on-site execution.</li>\n  <li>Support the planning and delivery of corporate events.</li>\n  <li>Maintain and enhance the Donor Management database to improve operational efficiency.</li>\n  <li>Handle inquiries related to donations-in-kind, sponsorships, and community projects.</li>\n  <li>Manage gift processing, donations-in-kind, and donor correspondence.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><br></h3>\n<h3><strong>Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Holds a degree in a relevant field.</li>\n  <li>Possesses at least 1 year of experience in fundraising and event management.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrates proven fundraising experience.</li>\n  <li>Strong in event planning, project management, and organizational skills.</li>\n  <li>A proactive, detail-oriented team player with excellent interpersonal and communication abilities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
